    public abstract class attribute_info
extends org.freeinternals.commonlib.core.FileComponent
implements GenerateTreeNodeClassFile
    Super class for attributes in class file. All attributes have the following format: 
        attribute_info {
        u2 attribute_name_index;
        u4 attribute_length;

        u1 info[attribute_length];
    }
    The contents in info is determined by attribute_name_index.
    Author:
    Amos Shi
    See Also:
    VM Spec: Attributes 
     java:S101 - Class names should comply with a naming convention --- We respect the name from JVM Spec instead
 java:S116 - Field names should comply with a naming convention --- We respect the name from JVM Spec instead

      • name

        public final String name
        Name of the attribute. It is one of the enum names in attribute_info.AttributeTypes.

      • attribute_name_index

        public final u2 attribute_name_index
        The attribute_name_index must be a valid unsigned 16-bit index into the ClassFile.constant_pool of the ClassFile, the ClassFile.constant_pool entry at attribute_name_index must be a CONSTANT_Utf8_info structure (CONSTANT_Utf8_info) representing the name of the attribute.

      • attribute_length

        public final u4 attribute_length
        The value of the attribute_length item indicates the length of the subsequent information in bytes. The length does not include the initial six bytes that contain the attribute_name_index and attribute_length items.
